        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Fiber Type Ratio</td>
          <td>More Type II = greater hypertrophy potential</td>
          <td>Train all fiber types; even Type I fibers can hypertrophy modestly</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Muscle Length</td>
          <td>Longer belly relative to bone = greater growth potential</td>
          <td>Gastrocnemius length predicts calf development ceiling</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
